The Edo state Commissioner for Environment and Sustainability, Dame Omoua Oni-Okpaku has resigned her appointment with the state government. Her resignation is coming barley one month after the Commissioner for Information and Orientation, Hon Paul Ohonbamu resigned his position. Although the official letter she tendered has not been made public as at the time of writing this report. When LEADERSHIP called her mobile number, the receiver said she is her Personal Assistant and that the story of her resignation is true. When asked what were the reasons for the resignation, she said it is only Oni-Okpaku herself that can respond to that. A top government official while confirming the development said they have been doubting her total commitment to the government. He said, “I am also just hearing that but in recent times we have been noticing her non-committal attitude to this government” Recall that the Chief of Staff to Governor Godwin Obaseki, Taiwo Akerele had in April resigned his appointment citing administrative inconsistencies in the government. In the last few weeks since Obaseki defected to the PDP, several Special Advisers, Senior Special Assistants and Special Assistants have resigned their appointment with the government. 